abstract: The Melbourne Argus reports a horrible massacre at Fiji. A Mr. LATTIN, who, it is said. was formerly a storekeeper in Melbourne, had shipped about 280 natives on board the French bark Moreu. Their ultimate destination was is believed, Queensland; but it seems that the Islanders rose en masse and mercilessly killed every white man on board with the exception as the mate. They then jumped overboard.

abstract: The Georgia muddle grows thicker and thicker, and it now looks as though it had degenerated into a quarrel between two factions of Republicans-Bullock and anti-Bullock. In the meantime both parties are telegraphing to members and Senators very vigorously, imploring them to stand by one side or the other.
